Zimbabwe Rail Wants Investors for $260 Million Program, ZBC Says

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-10-17T09:47:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/zimbabwe-rail-wants-investors-for-260-million-program-zbc-says.html
The state-owned National Railways of
 Zimbabwe  wants investors to help its ailing network, the state-
controlled  Zimbabwe Broadcasting Corp . said on its website,
citing railway General Manager Mike Karakadzai.  The rail company, known as NRZ, has refurbished 10
locomotives and 1,000 wagons and wants $260 million to
recapitalize operations and regain business in the Southern
African country and the region, Harare-based broadcaster said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 